'''IKAR''' is a [[Post-Denominational Judaism|post-denominational Jewish]] congregation and community founded in [[Los Angeles]] and led by Rabbi [[Sharon Brous]].<ref name=JDFMagic>[http://forward.com/news/168454/ikar-looks-to-build-without-losing-magic/ Jewish Daily Forward: "IKAR Looks To Build Without Losing Magic" by Rex Weiner] December 30, 2012</ref><ref>[http://jewishjournal.com/news/los_angeles/community/80634/ Jewish Journal: "How Different Is IKAR; Rabbi Sharon Brous Inspires Change … and Controversy" by Julie Gruenbaum] June 23, 2010</ref>
==History== IKAR ("essence" in Hebrew) was founded in 2004 by Rabbi [[Sharon Brous]] along with [[Melissa Balaban]], [[Joshua Avedon]], Stephanie Avedon, Celia Bernstein, [[Richard Foos]], Shari Foos, Nan Friedman, Adam Gilad, Lynn Kilroy, Ross Levinson, David Light, Paulette Light, Rachel Light, [[Paula Mazur]], Robert Mickelson, [[David N. Myers]], [[Andrea Blaugrund Nevins]], Yazmin Ibarlucea-Peebles, Mac Peebles, Amy Povich, Jeff Rake, [[Daniel Sokatch]], and Adam Wergeles, in a member's living room.<ref>[http://ikar-la.org/ask/our-story/ IKAR Our Story] retrieved October 24, 2017</ref><ref name=JDFMagic /><ref>[http://www.paideia-eu.org/programs/paideia-project-incubator/project-incubator-staff/ Paideia - The European Institute for Jewish Studies: "Project-Incubator Staff - Joshua Avedon"] retrieved October 24, 2017</ref><ref>[http://www.jewishjumpstart.org/documents/IKARrising_AvedonThesis2005.pdf Jewish Jumpstart: "IKAR RISING - A STUDY OF THE FIRST YEAR OF A NEW SPIRITUAL COMMUNITY IN LOS ANGELES] by Joshua H. Avedon] 2005</ref>
Prominent members include: *Michael Ellenberg, senior vice president at [[HBO]]<ref name=JDFMagic /> *[[Eric Garcetti]], mayor of [[Los Angeles]]<ref name=JDFMagic /> *[[Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver|Rick Jaffa]], screenwriter<ref name=TOIJur>{{Cite web|last=Staff|first=Toi|authorlink=|title=Jurassic World’s Jewish writers|publisher=[[Times of Israel]]|date=June 20, 2015|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/jurassic-worlds-jewish-writers/|accessdate=}}</ref> *[[David Nevins (television producer)|David Nevins]], president of entertainment for [[Showtime Networks]]<ref name=JDFMagic /> *[[Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver|Amanda Silver]], screenwriter<ref name=TOIJur />
